While the TechCrunch team is hunkered down watching Apple’s event today, we’re taking a short break from our more serious coverage to share our real-time reactions to the return of the iPhone SE. After Tim “Apple” Cook announced the new piece of hardware, our Slack room for the event had an immediate, and immediately-positive reaction. So, if you wanted to know what your TechCrunch is saying behind the scenes, here’s a look at our first take: <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-2281527" src="https://i0.wp.com/techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=680%2C559&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="680" height="559" srcset="https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png 1168w, https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=150,123 150w, https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=300,247 300w, https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=768,631 768w, https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=680,559 680w, https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-08-at-1.16.32-PM.png?resize=50,41 50w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" data-recalc-dims="1"> Haje, naturally, made a word joke. I lost my mind about the iPhone feature I miss the most, and both Devin and Zack scrambled for their wallets. Consider this a riposte to the general vibe that tech journalists only want phablet-style megaliths with seventeen cameras and the rest of the usual cruft. Mostly phones are for Twitter and avoiding email. So who doesn’t want a smaller, simpler device? Call it the revenge of the Peek. The iPhone SE returns  Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!